doc_summary_long: A new survey reported by the Centers for Disease Control And Prevention says rural women are having sex earlier than those living in urban areas. New data from the National Survey of Family Growth found 51 percent of women living in rural areas had their first sexual intercourse by age 16, compared to 41 percent of those in urban areas. Those percentages rose to 80 percent of rural women and 69 percent of urban women losing their virginity by age 18.
doc_summary_short: A new survey reported by the Centers for Disease Control And Prevention says rural women are having sex earlier than those living in urban areas.
doc_title: Rural women having sex earlier than women in the city, CDC report says
